# FTR-HIT-ONECALL — “One-call” Review: Hit → Review → Family → Blocks → Salesforce (no internal events)

## 1. Context & Goal

We replace internal choreography with a **single-call orchestration**: a hit triggers **one service** that opens the review, fetches family **by pages**, upserts blocks **in batches**, and feeds an **internal outbound queue** to Salesforce.
Goals: **idempotency**, **resume** after interruptions, **controlled volume** (\~400 members ≈ \~2,800 blocks), and **observability**.

## 2. Scope

**In**: single entrypoint; one active review per customer; paged family retrieval; batch block upserts (type-2 history + “current approved” gate); work table for progress; outbound queue to Salesforce.
**Out**: UI, advanced rule engine, party closure.

**Frozen assumptions**: one active review per customer; family via paged external API; new block version **only if** current is **approved**; may return **202 Accepted** with `workId` when time exceeds threshold.

