## 5. Data Model (diff)

Same as FR: `HIT_INBOX`, `REVIEW_INSTANCE`, `REVIEW_WORK`, `ROLE_BLOCK_POLICY`, `BLOCK`, `BLOCK_VERSION`, `REVIEW_TARGET`, `OUTBOX`.

## 6. Security & Privacy

Authenticate caller; no unnecessary personal data in logs/messages; encryption in transit/at rest; audit who/when/how many items processed.

## 7. Observability

Decision logs, progress logs (page/index), outbound metrics; traces per page and batch; alerts on outbound backlog and long batch times.

## 8. Testing & Acceptance (macro)

Unit (role→block, gate, versioning); Integration (paged family, batch writes, resume); E2E (idempotent hit, one active review, \~2,800 blocks, outbound queue resilience); Performance (tune page size and batch sizes).

